summary:
19. The Council will review measures in paragraphs 2, 4, 6, and 10 by 17 June 2004 to assess progress towards goals in paragraphs 5, 7, and 11 and decide whether to terminate them.

20. The Council will keep under review measures in paragraphs 6 and 10 to terminate them as soon as possible once conditions in paragraphs 7 and 11 are met.

21. A Committee of the Security Council will be established to: 
    (a) monitor implementation of measures;
    (b) seek information from States;
    (c) consider exemption requests;
    (d) designate individuals subject to measures;
    (e) make information publicly available;
    (f) consider pending issues; and
    (g) report to the Council.

22. A Panel of Experts will be established for 5 months to: 
    (a) assess implementation and violations;
    (b) assess progress towards goals; and
    (c) report to the Council by 30 May 2004.

23. UNMIL, UNAMSIL, and MINUCI will assist the Committee and Panel of Experts.

24. The international donor community is called upon to provide assistance for disarmament, demobilization, reintegration, and repatriation.

25. The National Transitional Government of Liberia is encouraged to sensitize the Liberian population to the rationale of the measures.

26. The Secretary-General will submit a report to the Council by 30 May 2004 on progress made.

27. The Council will remain seized of the matter.
